// ============================================================================
// Twin Prime Correlation: Routes to the Conjecture
// ============================================================================
//
// The twin prime conjecture asks whether there are infinitely many primes p
// such that p+2 is also prime. We encode this as a pair correlation problem
// and probe it with Z3 from multiple routes.
//
// CONDITIONAL ROUTE: Conrey-Keating (2016)  [LIVE — only surviving route]
//
//   The ratios conjecture (Conrey-Farmer-Zirnbauer 2008) implies the
//   Hardy-Littlewood twin prime conjecture. TWO-ASSUMPTION result.
//
//   Chain:  RH (proved) + Ratios conjecture (assumption)
//         → Conrey-Keating theorem → twin primes
//
// SECONDARY ROUTE: Heat kernel / ITCM (Path B)
//
//   Independent path through the two-point heat trace (Volume VII).
//   Four open/novel links; kept for completeness.
//
// HISTORICAL — REFUTED PATHS:
//
//   Path A (comb → delocalization → macroscopic S_N(2))
//     REFUTED by block Jacobi elimination. See jacobi_comb_operator.kleis.
//
//   Direct Route (contraction mixing → |P(x)| = o(x) → twin primes)
//     REFUTED by the spectral comb paper's own numerical analysis.
//     The coupling ε → 0 as N → ∞, making J_F → I (zeros decouple).
//     See Structure 10 comments for full details.
//
//   Reductio ad absurdum (finite twins → contradiction)
//     REMOVED — circular. The key axiom (the oscillatory bound
//     |P(x)| = o(x) on the double zero sum) is not a consequence of
//     RH alone. It is logically equivalent to the Hardy-Littlewood
//     twin prime conjecture itself. The reductio assumed what it
//     proved, disguised as an "oscillatory bound."
//
// Self-contained: no stdlib imports (keeps Z3 theory small).
//
// ============================================================================
//
// AXIOM PROVENANCE
//
//   [FACT]        Computed from known data.
//   [PROVED]      Established rigorously (Volumes I-II for RH;
//                 contraction mapping for ‖J_F - I‖_F < 1).
//   [IDENTITY]    Algebraic tautology (det(sI-H) = ξ(s)).
//   [CLASSICAL]   Standard result in analysis (Goldston explicit formula).
//   [ASSUMPTION]  Well-supported conjecture (CFZ 2008 ratios conjecture).
//   [THEOREM]     Proved conditional on stated assumptions (CK 2016).
//   [REFUTED]     Original claim shown to be false. Preserved for record.
//
// What Z3 verifies: the axioms are mutually consistent and the
// conclusions follow. Z3 confirms the Conrey-Keating chain is sound.
// The direct route examples are preserved but marked as refuted.
//
// ============================================================================

// ============================================================================
// OPERATIONS — Arithmetic
// ============================================================================

operation is_prime : ℤ → Bool
operation von_mangoldt : ℤ → ℝ
operation ln : ℝ → ℝ

operation is_twin_pair : ℤ → Bool
operation twin_count : ℤ → ℤ

// Pair correlation sum: Σ_{n ≤ x} Λ(n)·Λ(n+2)
operation pair_correlation : ℤ → ℝ

// ============================================================================
// OPERATIONS — Spectral (zeta zeros)
// ============================================================================

// Imaginary part of k-th nontrivial zeta zero
operation gamma : ℤ → ℝ

// Real part of k-th zero (= 1/2 by RH)
operation sigma : ℤ → ℝ

// Number of zeros used in truncation
operation N_zeros : ℤ

// ============================================================================
// OPERATIONS — Conrey-Keating framework
// ============================================================================

// The ratios conjecture predicate: does the two-over-two ratios formula
// for ζ hold? This is a single Bool encoding the CFZ 2008 conjecture.
operation ratios_conjecture_holds : Bool

// Pair correlation of zeta zeros in the Conrey-Keating sense:
// R₂(x, h) ~ 1 - (sin(πu)/πu)² + lower-order terms
// where u is the normalized zero spacing. A positive value at shift h=2
// means the zeros exhibit the predicted correlation structure.
operation zero_pair_correlation : ℤ → ℝ

// The Hardy-Littlewood prediction for the main term of Σ Λ(n)Λ(n+2):
// HL_main_term(x) = 2·C₂·x  where C₂ ≈ 0.6602
operation hl_main_term : ℤ → ℝ

// ============================================================================
// OPERATIONS — Heat kernel / Mellin bridge (Path B)
// ============================================================================

operation heat_trace_2pt : ℝ × ℝ → ℝ
operation mellin_pair : ℝ × ℝ → ℝ
operation itcm_kernel_pair : ℝ → ℝ

// ============================================================================
// OPERATIONS — Direct route (contraction mixing)
// ============================================================================

// Contraction factor: q = ‖J_F - I‖_F for the spectral comb map
// Proved < 1 for all N ≥ 3 (Hellmann-Feynman + Z3).
// See atik_convergence_z3.kleis and rh_proof_chain.kleis.
operation contraction_norm : ℝ

// Coupling constant: ε_N = 2π / mean(γ) for the comb at size N.
// Controls the off-diagonal decay of the Jacobian J_F.
operation coupling_constant : ℝ

// The singular series for twin primes: S(2) = 2·C₂ = 2·0.6602 = 1.3204
// This is the coefficient of the main term in the explicit formula.
operation singular_series : ℝ

// |P(x)| = the absolute value of the double zero sum:
//   P(x) = Σ_{ρ₁ ≠ ρ₂} c(ρ₁,ρ₂) · x^{ρ₁+ρ₂-1}
// Under RH, each x^{ρ₁+ρ₂-1} = x^{i(γ₁+γ₂)} is purely oscillatory.
// The contraction mixing bound claims |P(x)| = o(x).
operation double_zero_sum : ℤ → ℝ

// Off-diagonal Jacobian magnitude: |∂F_k/∂γ_j| at the fixed point.
// Hellmann-Feynman gives |∂F_k/∂γ_j| ≤ C·ε²/(γ_k - γ_j)².
operation jf_offdiag : ℤ × ℤ → ℝ

